*******************************Day 5: SELinux Installation and Configuration***************************

Install the required SELinux packages
Temporarily disable SELinux via the config file (no reboot)
Ensure SELinux stays disabled after a scheduled reboot
Disregard the current command-line status

--------------------------------
ANS : 

SSH into the app server from the jump host

Checked the OS Version
confirmed the server’s operating system to determine which package manager to use.
cat /etc/*release


installed the SELinux Package
yum install -y selinux-policy selinux-policy-targeted

selinux-policy → The base rule set for SELinux
selinux-policy-targeted → Default policy that targets high-risk services

Permanently Disabled SELinux
sudo vi /etc/selinux/config

#Once the file was opened, Changed
SELINUX=enforcing

#to 

SELINUX=disabled


Verified the Config Change
grep SELINUX= /etc/selinux/config
